body(data-spy="scroll", data-target=".subnav", data-offset="100")
  div#banner_bg"
    h1 MAJURO.JS
    h3
      span Many websites have data.
      br
      span At MajuroJS.org,
      em you
      span have data.

  div#information
    div#main_nav_cont.subnav
      div#nav_cont
        ul.nav.nav-pills
          li
            a(href="#app") App
          li
            a(href="#cities") Cities
          li
            a(href="#faq") FAQ
            
  div#wrapper
    div#main_container.info
      div#app.main_cont
        div
          p Majuro.JS helps you make detailed, interactive maps with open buildings data.
          p It's free and open source.
        
        h2 It couldn't be easier
        div
          ol
            li
              h3 Draw a neighborhood.
              p Drag points on the blue shape to cover any part of the city.
              img(src="images/draw_shot.png", width="700")
              br

            li
              h3 Drop markers to color-code buildings.
              p Click a building to add a photo or description.
              img(src="images/editor_shot.png", width="700")
              br
              img(src="images/click_editor.png", width="400", style="margin-left:150px;")
              br
              p Your custom map is saved here on MajuroJS.org.

            li
              h3 Data for Download
              p Download your map for Google Earth, share a KML or GeoJSON file, or set up your own site on Github Pages.
              img(src="images/in_earth.png", width="400", style="margin-left:150px;")
              br
        div#finish_line_cont

      div#cities.main_cont
        h1 Cities
        p Some sources include addresses, build dates, and height of buildings. You'll get that data, too.
        ul
          li
            a(href="/make?src=allegheny") Allegheny County (Pittsburgh), PA
          li
            a(href="/make?src=chicago") Chicago, IL
            span + (address, build date, height)
          li
            a(href="/make?src=lancaster") Lancaster County, PA
          li
            a(href="/make?src=oakland") Oakland (partial), CA
            span + (name)
          li
            a(href="/make?src=philadelphia") Philadelphia, PA
          li
            a(href="/make?src=savannah") Savannah, GA
          li
            a(href="/make?src=seattle") Seattle, WA
        p Buildings data was collected under open data licenses. There is no official endorsement or maintenance of this site by these cities and counties.
        
        div#finish_line_cont

      div#faq.main_cont
        h1 FAQ
        div
          h4 How can I use the data?
          p This site links to each city's open data policy.
          p If you have questions or need the data for anything mission-critical, ask the city.
          hr

          h4 What if my city isn't included?
          p Reach out to your city and county GIS departments. It's possible that they may not have buildings data, or that one may have better data than the other.</p>
          p If you get permission to publish the data freely on this site, please have an official send a written data policy.</p>
          hr

          h4 How do I add my data?
          p Send a shapefile, KML, or a link to your city's open data site.
          hr

          h4 Is this open source?
          p The entire site is open source.
          a(href="https://github.com/mapmeld/majurojs") Source code on Github
          hr
          
          h4 Can I map a whole city with this?
          p Maps on Majuro.js are vector-based, so several hundred or thousands of buildings can slow down web browsers.
          p
            span For large projects, try downloading the data as KML, then upload it to&nbsp;
            a(href="http://cartodb.com") CartoDB
            span &nbsp;and edit it through&nbsp;
            a(href="https://github.com/codeforamerica/NeighborDiff") NeighborDiff
            span .
          hr

          h4 How did this project get started?
          p
            span I am Nick Doiron, @mapmeld on&nbsp;
            a(href="http://twitter.com/mapmeld") Twitter
            span &nbsp;and&nbsp;
            a(href="http://github.com/mapmeld") Github
            span . Majuro.js is based on projects that I made for the City of Macon, GA during my Code for America fellowship, particularly:&nbsp;
            a(href="https://github.com/codeforamerica/geodata-checkout") GeoData Checkout
            span &nbsp;and&nbsp;
            a(href="https://github.com/codeforamerica/NeighborDiff") NeighborDiff
            span .
        
        div#finish_line_cont

